üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. The primary objective of a compliance audit is to ensure:
A. System performance
B. Legal and regulatory adherence
C. Network availability
D. Application scalability

2. Which of the following best defines compliance?
A. Following company culture
B. Adhering to internal and external rules
C. Improving productivity
D. Enhancing security tools

3. Cybersecurity challenges mainly arise due to:
A. High employee salaries
B. Rapid technological changes
C. Reduced competition
D. Static threat environment

4. Which audit checks adherence to organizational policies?
A. External audit
B. Financial audit
C. Internal audit
D. Forensic audit

5. Which of the following is NOT a type of security audit?
A. Internal audit
B. External audit
C. Compliance audit
D. Performance appraisal audit

6. Audit decision factors primarily help in:
A. Selecting firewall vendors
B. Determining audit scope and depth
C. Increasing audit fees
D. Eliminating audit documentation

7. The first phase of a security audit is:
A. Reporting
B. Remediation
C. Planning
D. Evidence collection

8. Internal audit teams are generally responsible to:
A. External regulators
B. Organization‚Äôs management
C. Law enforcement
D. Customers

9. Which principle ensures auditors are unbiased?
A. Confidentiality
B. Independence
C. Integrity
D. Professional care

10. Auditor personal abilities mainly include:
A. Coding skills
B. Soft skills and analytical thinking
C. Marketing knowledge
D. Hardware troubleshooting

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which cybersecurity challenge most impacts compliance today?
A. Legacy hardware
B. Dynamic threat landscape
C. Excess documentation
D. Fixed policies

12. Compliance audits mainly focus on:
A. Identifying attackers
B. Checking control effectiveness against standards
C. Penetration testing
D. Malware detection

13. An external audit is generally performed by:
A. Internal employees
B. Third-party independent auditors
C. System administrators
D. SOC analysts

